                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has our opinion this morning in Case 13-719, Dart Cherokee Basin Operating Company v. Owens."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.827,
                        "stop": 375.864,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.827,
                                "stop": 17.197,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case concerns the removal of a civil action from a State Court to a Federal Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.197,
                                "stop": 25.723,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "To launch removal the defendant files in the Federal Court a notice stating the grounds for removal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.723,
                                "stop": 35.26,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "When removal is based on the party\u0027s diverse citizenship, an amount in controversy requirement must be met."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.26,
                                "stop": 51.239,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "To meet that requirement does it suffice to allege the requisite amount plausibly or must the defendant incorporate into the notice of removal evidence proving the allegation?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.239,
                                "stop": 54.054,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That is the question this case presents."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.054,
                                "stop": 78.067,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Brandon Owens, plaintiff below and respondent here, filed a class action in the Kansas State Court alleging that defendants Dart Cherokee Basin Operating Company and a related company (collectively Dart) underpaid royalties owed to class members under certain oil and gas leases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.067,
                                "stop": 87.567,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The complaint sought a fair and reasonable amount to compensate class members for the alleged underpayments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 87.567,
                                "stop": 98.934,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Invoking federal jurisdiction under the Class Action Fairness Act, Dart removed the case from State Court to the US District Court for the District of Kansas."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 98.934,
                                "stop": 108.142,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "To qualify for federal adjudication under that Act the case must involve an amount in controversy exceeding $5 million."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.142,
                                "stop": 117.713,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Dart\u0027s notice of removal stated that the alleged underpayments totaled more than $8.2 million."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.713,
                                "stop": 121.083,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Owens moved to remand the case to State Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.083,
                                "stop": 131.345,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Dart\u0027s notice of removal was deficient, Owens maintained, because it failed to include proof that the amount at stake exceeded $5 million."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.345,
                                "stop": 143.186,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In response, Dart submitted a calculation by one of its executive offices estimating that the amount in controversy exceeded $11 million."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.186,
                                "stop": 151.001,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Without challenging Dart\u0027s calculation, Owens urged that Dart\u0027s submission came too late."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.001,
                                "stop": 162.646,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The deficient notice of removal, Owens urged, could not be cured by post-removal documentation of the amount in controversy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.646,
                                "stop": 174.754,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Reading Tenth Circuit precedent to require evidence in the notice of removal itself the District Court granted Owens\u0027 motion and sent the case back to the State Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.754,
                                "stop": 180.302,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Ordinarily remand orders may not be appealed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.302,
                                "stop": 185.339,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Congress made an exception to that general rule in the Class Action Fairness Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 185.339,
                                "stop": 195.522,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Act gives the Courts of Appeals discretion to review an order granting or denying a remand motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 195.522,
                                "stop": 205.046,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Citing this provision, Dart petitioned the Tenth Circuit for permission to appeal, dividing two-to-one, the Tenth Circuit denied permission."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 205.046,
                                "stop": 215.989,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We granted review to resolve a division among the Circuits on the question whether a notice of removal must include evidence proving the amount in controversy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 215.989,
                                "stop": 222.816,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We held that no evidentiary submission need be made at the removal notice stage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 222.816,
                                "stop": 232.974,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The statute in point instructs that a notice of removal shall contain a short and plain statement of the ground for removal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 232.974,
                                "stop": 240.752,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That language tracks the general pleading requirements stated in Rule 8(a) of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 240.752,
                                "stop": 253.528,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "By borrowing the Rule 8(a) standard, Congress clarified that Courts should apply to removal allegations the same liberal rules they apply to other matters of pleading."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 253.528,
                                "stop": 274.835,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Just at the plaintiff\u0027s amount in controversy allegation is accepted if made in good faith, so a defendant\u0027s amount in controversy allegation should be accepted when not contested by the plaintiff or questioned by the Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 274.835,
                                "stop": 287.42,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "An amicus brief filed by Public Citizen asserted a jurisdictional impediment to our review and alleged insurmountable obstacle flagged by neither party."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 287.42,
                                "stop": 300.163,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Because review of a remand order is discretionary, Public Citizen urged, and the Tenth Circuit did not say why it declined review, we have no authority to take up the question presented."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 300.163,
                                "stop": 319.28,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our close inspection however reveals that the two issues Public Citizen invites us to separate, whether the Tenth Circuit abused its discretion in denying review, and whether the District Court\u0027s remand order was erroneous do not pose genuinely discrete inquiries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 319.28,
                                "stop": 326.467,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Both issues turn on the answer to the very same question, what must the removal notice contain?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 326.467,
                                "stop": 348.204,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "If the notice need not contain evidence the District Court erred, and more important the Tenth Circuit abused its discretion by effectively making the opposing view the law of the Circuit, thereby disarming defendants from challenging that erroneous view and consequently shielding the error from correction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 348.204,
                                "stop": 354.821,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Kennedy and Kagan joined."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 354.821,
                                "stop": 360.566,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Save for the last sentence, Justice Thomas also joins Justice Scalia\u0027s opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 360.566,
                                "stop": 364.59,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In addition, Justice Thomas has filed the dissenting opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 364.59,
                                "stop": 375.864,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "As the dissenters think we lack authority to take up this case, they express no view on the answer to the question presented."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
